OL,4,Chave been distracted' by police
OL,6,FToday, Cumbria Police's collisions
OL,7,Finvestigator Steven Wakefield told the
OL,8,Fcourt that he estimated the van to be
OL,9,Ftravelling at around 40mph when it
OL,10,Fleft the road and collided with a tree.
OL,12,FHe added that this is well below the
OL,13,Fnational speed limit of 60, though it
OL,14,Fwas likely close to the maximum speed
OL,15,Frequired to successfully make the bend
OL,16,Fin the road.
OL,18,FHe added that there is evidence of
OL,19,Fimpairment because the driver was
OL,20,Fintoxicated with drugs and alcohol.
